	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=103648880286276>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103648880286276>RE: help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103648880286276#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Nov 5th 4:33 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=114334><span id= >Recursion</span></a><br><span id=notbold>35 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.99]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/creationguides/Bard.asp" target=_new>http://eq.crgaming.com/creationguides/Bard.asp</a><br><br>Follow that link for some good information on creating a bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;Honestly it doesn't matter so much.  Some of the races have special abilities like hide or safe fall, but these are all skills bards get eventually anyway.  They all have fairly good faction.  Human's have no infravision.<br><br>In regards to stats.  I would put a sizable portion of them into stamina.  While charisma, dexteriy, and even strength are more important, stamina gear is harder to get ahold of.  At level 50, I have like 120 str, 120 dex, 255 cha, but only 93 stamina.  This means I don't have much in the way of hit points.  Also, in melee combat, I get tired very quickly.<br><br>Good luck with your bard.  One of the most useful classes in the game! =)<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
